dalserver.conf

Class FITSHeaderKeywords

  • java.lang.Object
    • dalserver.conf.FITSHeaderKeywords
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    NTFITSHeaderKeywords

    public abstract class FITSHeaderKeywords
extends java.lang.Object
    a simple container for FITS Header keywords. Header values are accessed given a HDU number and keyword name. The primary HDU has a number equal to 0. This class is abstract to allow for different storage implementations, perhaps leveraging an underlying FITS library class. For example, the NTFITSHeaderKeywords class wraps around a list of nom.tam.fits.Header instances.

      • getStringValue

        public abstract java.lang.String getStringValue(int hduIndex,
                              java.lang.String keywordName,
                              java.lang.String defval)
        return a string value for the requested header card. If the value is not explicitly of a string type, the raw string value from the header will be returned.
        Parameters:
        hduIndex - the index for the HDU to extract the value from, where 0 is the primary (first) HDU.
        keywordName - the name of the header card to retrieve a value for
        defval - a default value to return if the keyword is not found
        Returns:
        String a string rendering of the value or deval if the keyword is not found.
